#
# All families below are DERIVED FROM existing matrix QCT columns
# like: p16dimer.Hbond.stackingraw, p8monomer.HLgap.eVraw, ...
#
# Families (enable one at a time for clean ablations):
#   A) Oligomer non-additivity   eng.qct_nonadd.*
#   B) Cas9-seed regional QCT    eng.qct_seed.*
#   C) Pruned regional QCT       eng.qct_pruned.*
#   D) Hotspot / peak location   eng.qct_hotspot.*
#
# NOT derived here (different kind of work — see):
#   E) SHAP analysis cells  ->  crispr_clean_shap_cells.py
#   F) Human transfer       ->  run this same script on human CSV
#
# Usage:
#   1. Set INPUT_CSV / OUTPUT_CSV / ACTIVE_FAMILIES below
#   2. python qct_experimental_features.py
#   3. In crispr_clean.py CELL 3, point DATA_PATH at OUTPUT_CSV
#   4. Re-run cells 4-7
#
# Tip: set ACTIVE_FAMILIES to exactly ONE family per experiment.
# ============================================================

